2.1 Groups
==========

A group definition has the form:

   name {    settings ...  }

   An optional semicolon may appear after the closing brace.

   Groups can contain any number of settings, and can be nested to
arbitrary depth.


File: libconfig.info,  Node: Assignments,  Next: Arrays,  Prev: Groups,  Up: Configuration Files

2.2 Assignments
===============

An assignment has the form:

   name = value ;

   The trailing semicolon is required.

   The value may be a simple value or an array.


File: libconfig.info,  Node: Arrays,  Next: Integer Values,  Prev: Assignments,  Up: Configuration Files

2.3 Arrays
==========

An array has the form:

   [ value, value ... ]

   An array may have zero or more elements, but the elements must all
be of the same type.


